05204nam a22008295i 9783110895131DE-B159720220629043637.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220629t20102005gw     fo  d z      fre d  a97831108951317 a10.1515/97831108951312doi  a(DE-B1597)43648  a(OCoLC)999372957  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 afre  agwcDE 4aHM511b.B68 2005eb 7aSOC0260002bisacsh04a301.01222  aMP 80002rvk0(DE-625)rvk/123409:1 aBourdieu, Pierre, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut13aLe métier de sociologue :bPréalables épistémologiques. Contient un entretien avec Pierre Bourdieu recueilli par Beate Krais /cPierre Bourdieu, Jean-Claude Chamboredon, Jean-Claude Passeron.  aReprint 2010 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter Mouton, c[2010] 4c©2005  a1 online resource (357 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aTextes de Sciences Sociales ;v100tI-XX -- tPréface à la deuxième édition -- tSommaire -- tINTRODUCTION. ÉPISTÉMOLOGIE ET MÉTHODOLOGIE -- tPREMIÈRE PARTIE. LA RUPTURE -- tDEUXIÈME PARTIE. LA CONSTRUCTION DE L’OBJET -- tTROISIÈME PARTIE. LE RATIONALISME APPLIQUÉ -- tCONCLUSION. SOCIOLOGIE DE LA CONNAISSANCE ET ÉPISTÉMOLOGIE -- tREMARQUES SUR LE CHOIX DES TEXTES -- tAvant-propos -- tINTRODUCTION: Épistémologie et méthodologie -- t1. La rupture -- t2. La construction de l'objet -- t3. Le rationalisme appliqué -- tConclusion: Sociologie de la connaissance et épistémologie -- tLISTE DES TEXTES -- tIndications de lectures complementaires -- tIndex des noms -- tIndex des thèmes0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe work of the French sociologist Pierre Bourdieu has emerged as one of the most substantial and innovative bodies of theory and research in contemporary social science. Le métier de sociologue, both a textbook and an original contribution to epistemology in social science, focuses on a basic problem of sociological research: the necessity of an epistemological break with the preconstructed objects social practice offers to the researcher. Pierre Bourdieu and his co-authors argue in the epistemological tradition of scholars like Bachelard, Canguilhem, Koyré, a tradition that identifies the construction of the object as being the fundamental scientific act. Their way of discussing the issue makes it accessible not only to academics and experts of epistemology, but also to advanced students of social science, using for illustration a wide range of texts from the various social sciences as well as from philosophy of science. The fifth edition of Le métier de sociologue contains an interview with Pierre Bourdieu conducted by Beate Krais in 1988.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aSociologyxMethodology. 4aSoziologie /Beruf. 4aSoziologie. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aBourdieu, Pierre.  aSociology /profession.  aSociology.1 aChamboredon, Jean-Claude, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aKrais, Beate.1 aPasseron, Jean-Claude, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Social Sciences 2000 - 2014z9783110638080oZDB-23-GSS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Backlist 2000-2015z978311074296108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2005z9783110277111oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2005z9783110276886oZDB-23-DGA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-DITION: BEST OF LINGUISTICSz9783110233940oZDB-23-DGO0 cprintz978311017429840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311089513140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/978311089